article.headline: Fields' 27 help Arkansas State knock off Southern Miss 78-71

images.name: Izaiyah Nelson gets up for the beautiful slam
images.caption: Izaiyah Nelson gets up for the beautiful slam

article.linkText: Fields' 27 help Arkansas State knock off Southern Miss 78-71
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. -- — Caleb Fields' 27 points helped Arkansas State defeat Southern Miss 78-71 on Wednesday night. Fields also contributed eight assists for the Red Wolves (9-13, 5-5 Sun Belt Conference). Derrian Ford scored 13 points and added 10 rebounds. Izaiyah Nelson was 4 of 11 shooting and 3 of 4 from the free throw line to finish with 11 points, while adding 12 rebounds and three blocks. The Golden Eagles (12-10, 6-4) were led by Victor Iwuakor, who recorded 17 points, 12 rebounds and three blocks. Donovan Ivory and Austin Crowley finished with 17 points apiece. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
